  "description": "Nils Oskar Teofil Fridlund (1883-10-13) was a Swedish high school teacher. He was born in Malmö, son of headmaster Jöns F. and Elsa Ohlsson. He completed his high studies in Malmö and obtained his Bachelor of Arts in Lund. He studied in Germany, England, Austria, Holland, and Denmark for biblical studies. He worked as a substitute lecturer and teacher in various cities and schools before becoming a teacher in mother tongue, German, and English at Växjö högre allmänna läroverk in 1917. He worked as a librarian at Växjö diocese and Gymnasium Library and as a city librarian. He was a member of various organizations and was awarded the Royal Order of Vasa (RVO) in 1938."
